        "manager": "aleksi.pohjolainen@tretton37.com",
        "orgUnit": "/Employees",
        "mainText": "<p>When I'm not reading about new technologies or trying out new frameworks, I spend my time at the golf course (when the weather allows for it) or in the gym.</p><p>These activities suits me perfectly, because when I'm walking up to that 250m drive, or catching my breath after bench-pressing 100kgs (-40...), I utilise these small moments to think about my current projects.</p><p>Those moments often generate small chunks of code or solution epiphanies. The hard part is to remember those eureka-bursts and bring them to work the next day...</p>  ",
