        "manager": "johan.lundborg@tretton37.com",
        "orgUnit": "/Employees",
        "mainText": "<p>​My fascination with the Internet began at the end of the past century, when I was still in high school, and it’s been going strong to this day. Ever since experiencing it for the first time, I knew I wanted to do something for the web. </p><p>Making websites quickly turned into an obsession, as it always presented me with new challenges and allowed me to keep learning and improving. Once I learned I could actually get paid for doing this, I realised the obsession was actually nothing short of a blessing.</p><p>Being paid for solving problems in a creative fashion is awesome, but the best part of my calling is being in the unique position to make a difference for people and organisations, customers and businesses.</p><p>Combine that with working with amazing people, and you got yourself a winning combination. That’s why, after years of working solo or as a member of in-house design teams, I decided to join tretton37.</p><p>Besides work, I enjoy hiking and bike riding, whenever weather allows it. Reading and listening to podcasts, as well as solving sudoku, helps me keep a strong mental game, whereas weightlifting and yoga do the same for the body.</p>  ",
