        "phoneNumber": "+46729000451",
        "office": "Stockholm",
        "manager": "johan.lundborg@tretton37.com",
        "orgUnit": "/Employees",
        "mainText": "<p>My path to becoming a developer and furthermore landing a job at tretton37 has been anything but straight. Having spent the first five years of my career managing digital projects, an Indian subsidiary office in Mumbai, and finally a team of digital analysts, I jumped on the opportunity to follow a growing dream of specialising in software development.</p><p>In most other industries this kind of transition is probably nowhere near as painless but in IT all you really need is your passion and a dedication to learning. As a learning-oriented person, this is an environment I thrive in.</p><p>My main driving force is the feeling of overcoming challenges and doing so with like minded people. The more sweat and tears go in, the better the feeling once all of those hours spent researching, testing and building pay off!</p><p>As far as tech goes, I love full-stack development in Typescript, NodeJS and React, but apart from that I try to pick the best tool for the job.</p><p>When I’m not busy hacking away at work or on some personal project, my next biggest passion is music. Be it playing my Fender Stratocaster or expanding my vinyl collection. I’m an avid concert goer and do my best to mosh a few times every year.</p>  ",
