        "office": "Helsingborg",
        "manager": "jenny.fergeus@tretton37.com",
        "orgUnit": "/Employees",
        "mainText": "<p>Since being introduced to programming at a young age, I've enjoyed developing software as a hobby and profession. After completing my studies I spent 5-6 years working as a backend Java developer and consultant. Then the iPhone was released, and it brought mobile development into my purview.</p><p>It allowed me to combine programming with other interests such as graphic design and user experience, and I was offered to work as an iOS-developer. This is essentially what I still do most of the time, and I very much still enjoy it.</p><p>Outside of work I enjoy craft beer and music concerts.</p> ",
