        "manager": "andreas.nilsson@tretton37.com",
        "orgUnit": "/Employees",
        "mainText": "<p>When the time came for me to make the big choice of what I wanted to study at upper secondary school, my mom told me I should apply for something tech oriented. I told her \"I do like computers, but I don't want to become a nerd!\". I ended up studying to be a chef.</p><p>After three fun and hard-working years as a chef, I was done kidding myself and I applied to study Computer Sciences with an focus on application development at Malmö University. I am now proud to be both a nerd and a ninja!</p><p>I prefer to code in JavaScript, but I have some experience with Java and Android. I love to learn new things, so I have tried out a lot of other languages and frameworks, and will continue to do so.</p><p>When I'm not coding, you can often find me gaming - both TV and computer. You could also find me in the kitchen brewing some nice beers (might be drinking some too). I also like to hang with friends, or with my spouse and daughter.</p> ",
