        "phoneNumber": "+46736612092",
        "office": "Helsingborg",
        "manager": "jenny.fergeus@tretton37.com",
        "orgUnit": "/Employees",
        "mainText": "<p>Ever since I can remember, I have had a drive to create things. When I came into contact with computers and programming, it was not an instant match, but during my studies I found out that I could create a homepage and host it on the school server - so I did. One thing led to another, and I started working as a web developer between classes. Then came the dot-com-era, and suddenly there was lots of work and loads fun projects everywhere. I have been hooked ever since.</p><p>I like to deliver quality code for the developers that come after me and quality features for users of the application. Taking a task a few extra miles isn't always asked for, but always gives me a good feeling when it can be done despite a tight deadline.</p><p>After work I like to hang out with my family, spend time in nature and play games. I also enjoy a bit of 3D-modelling and donate a bit of work to the community thingiverse. Whatever I'm up to, I'm always creating things.</p> ",
