        "phoneNumber": "+46722133739",
        "office": "Stockholm",
        "manager": "johan.lundborg@tretton37.com",
        "orgUnit": "/Employees",
        "mainText": "<p>After being kicked out from the land of meat and football - Argentina - for being a vegetarian and not understanding that sport at all, I decided to start my career as a software engineer in sunny Barcelona, Spain.</p><p>I spent several years working as a XAML-based developer, Scrum Master and Project Lead in the healthcare and pharmaceutical industry. A new challenge presented itself in moving to Sweden and working at tretton37, so I took it!</p><p>When I’m not doing geeky things, you’ll often find me visiting natural environments, creating video games, playing sports (not football) or pretending to be a good heavy-metal-cover cellist. Ok… yes, half of those are pretty geeky – but let’s just pretend they’re not.</p> ",
