        "mainText": "<p>Tech nerd, sports nerd, Tolkien nerd. Simply put, a nerd!</p><p>My love for tech and especially computers started very early in my life when my best friends Dad bought a computer. We started to play games on it, and after a while started to make some simple programs and games.</p><p>My love for sports also started very early and I have played and watched sports for as long as I can remember. I love to watch football and ice hockey and I love to play floorball and padel. I am also a coach for my sons floorball team.</p><p>My love for Tolkien started when the Peter Jackson films came out in 2001. I absolutely loved the films, and still do, and wanted to know more about middle earth and hence read Lord of the Rings and all the other books in the legendarium.</p><p>I have been in the IT and consultancy business since the beginning of the century. Between 2003-2007 I got to travel the world, spending approximately 200 days a year abroad. It was a wonderful time because I got to see a lot of places in the world that I otherwise wouldn't have gotten to see. In 2007 I started out as a consultant with assignments such as Integrator, DBA-admin and developer. After four years of consulting (and two parental leaves) I got the chance to be a part of the management team at a company in Malmö as a Consultant Manager and I held this position for seven years until the summer of 2018. After that, I was for a brief time the CEO of a small consultancy company and Partner Manager at another company. Then tretton37 came knocking and I didn’t hesitate for very long to jump on board as Business Developer / Key Account Manager.</p><p> </p><p>I am an easy going guy and I like to have fun! In my spare time I like to work out, watch sports, listen to music and hang out with family and friends. I live in Virentofta in eastern Malmö with my wife Anna, my son Axel and my daughter Sofia.</p> ",
