        "mainText": "<p>I have been creating things for as long as I can remember. It all started with Lego, and continued on to music before finally ending up in the wonderful world of programming. Working as an audiologist, I spent pretty much all of my spare time for eight years creating games and simulators, so finally my friends told me to go professional. I did and I haven’t looked back since – I haven’t cut down on my spare time programming though!</p><p>Creating apps with Xamarin, .Net and openFrameworks is what I usually go for, but I love diving into any kind of project. In fact, I have yet to find a platform or language that doesn’t get me curious and hungry for more. </p><p>I always try to keep an open creative mind, and find inspiration in my family, playing video games and biking in the woods. ​</p> ",
